    
# Please use the following guidelines to format all your commit messages:
# 
#     <type>(<scope>): <subject>	<== HEADER *
#     <BLANK LINE>
#     <body>						<== BODY *
#     <BLANK LINE>
#     <footer>						<== FOOTER *
# 
# Please note that:
#  - The HEADER is a single line of max. 50 characters       
#       + <type> type of change made from the following list:
#             chore, docs, feat, fix, refactor, style, test
#       + <scope> can be anything specifying the place of the commit change
#       + <subject> is a very short description of the change
#  - The BODY should include reason for change and contrast previous behavior   
#  - The FOOTER should contain any information about Breaking       
#    Changes and/or reference issue/tickets relating to change
